ilve-umdi10qns3bgg,ilve-umdi10qns3bgp,ilve-umdi10qns3bkb,ilve-umdi10qns3bkc,ilve-umdi10qns3bkg,ilve-umdi10qns3bkp,ilve-umdi10qns3bub,ilve-umdi10qns3buc,ilve-umdi10qns3bug,ilve-umdi10qns3bup,ilve-umdi10qns3egb,ilve-umdi10qns3egc,ilve-umdi10qns3egg,ilve-umdi10qns3egp,ilve-umdi10qns3mbb,ilve-umdi10qns3mbc,ilve-umdi10qns3mbg,ilve-umdi10qns3mbp,ilve-umdi10qns3mgb,ilve-umdi10qns3mgc,ilve-umdi10qns3mgg,ilve-umdi10qns3mgp,ilve-umdi10qns3rab,ilve-umdi10qns3rac,ilve-umdi10qns3rag,ilve-umdi10qns3rap,ilve-umdi10qns3ssb,ilve-umdi10qns3ssc,ilve-umdi10qns3ssg,ilve-umdi10qns3ssp,ilve-umdi10qns3whb,ilve-umdi10qns3whc,ilve-umdi10qns3whg,ilve-umdi10qns3whp\", \"Variant Count\": 80, \"Variant HTML\": \" <div aria-hidden=\\\"true\\\" aria-labelledby=\\\"station-tabs-tab_description\\\" class=\\\"station-tabs-tabpanel station-tabs-default-tabpanel\\\" id=\\\"station-tabs-tabpanel_description\\\" role=\\\"tabpanel\\\"> <div class=\\\"station-tabs-tabcontent\\\"><div class=\\\"station-tabs-tabcontent\\\"><p>The Majestic 40\\\" induction range combines cutting-edge technology with traditional Italian design. This range has dual 2.3 + 1.52 cu, six precise and effective element zones. sq. total oven capacity, 4.3-inch full touch oven control display, and easily cleaned enamel oven cavity.</p><p>Pre-Order (90\\u2013120 Days)</p><div><p><strong>Magnificent</strong></p><p>The eye-catching range cooker that makes your kitchen distinctive.</p><p></p><p>Majestic is a daring, expert representation of the ideal range cooker, combining beauty and functionality. A free-standing statement piece with a style that features rounded lines, expertly crafted details, exquisite finishes, solutions, and technologies straight from the world of professional cooking that instantly takes center stage and blends into any setting.</p><p></p><p>The rounded shapes of majestic range cookers, which are crafted from pure steel with meticulously made details, make them aesthetically pleasing appliances.</p><p></p><p>They are genuine works of art, created for your home's kitchen. They come with exquisite metallic finishes and are offered in a variety of chosen colors or in RAL Classic shades upon request. They are available in a variety of sizes (from 30 to 60 inches) and provide numerous setup options.</p><p></p><ul><li>indicator of residual heat</li><li>Automatic stop timer</li><li>Bridge monitoring</li><li>Booster function</li><li>Slide controls</li><li>Child safety</li><li>4.3-inch full-touch display</li><li>Protection from liquid spills and overheating</li><li>precise electronic temperature regulation</li><li>Soft-closing door and drawer</li><li>Quick start</li></ul><p></p><hr/><p></p><p><strong>Product Technologies</strong></p><p></p><p>Aesthetics are important, but that's not all. To cook well and enjoyably, the best technologies are required. In order to consistently ensure the highest level of satisfaction, ILVE puts all of its research and experience to work for you, providing solutions that combine optimal performance with maximum simplicity, safety, and user-friendliness.</p><p></p><p><strong>Cooktop (Hob) Technology</strong></p><p></p><p><strong>(Hob) Induction Cooktop</strong></p><p>Majestic induction cooktops (hobs) combine the newest technology with an elegant and sophisticated design to provide a quick, safe, and practical method of cooking. Induction offers a number of benefits, including ease of cleaning, energy conservation, safety, flexible temperature control, and cooking speed, all of which make it easier to prepare meals and recipes.</p><p></p><p><strong>Indicator of Remaining Heat</strong></p><p>indicates that the glass is hot, so care should be taken when handling it and putting objects on it to prevent damage.</p><p></p><p><strong>Automatic Stop Timer</strong></p><p>Once the predetermined amount of time has passed, the active zone is turned off.</p><p></p><p><strong>Bridge Management</strong></p><p>This feature allows induction cooktops (hobs) to simultaneously control two adjacent zones as if they were a single zone with a single command.</p><p></p><p><strong>Booster Function</strong></p><p>enables you to concentrate all of the induction cooktop's (hob's) power in the designated zone to shorten boiling and cooking times.</p><p></p><p><strong>Slide Controls</strong></p><p>With the help of this practical \\\"touch control\\\" system, you can, for instance, change the operating temperature by moving your finger from right to left or vice versa.</p><p></p><p><strong>Child Safety</strong></p><p>The induction cooktop (hob) does not turn on by turning on the controls once this function has been set and until it is disabled.</p><p></p><p><strong>Liquid Spill Protection and Overheating</strong></p><p>A safety device trips and stops operation if the cooktop (hob) overheats or spills liquid.</p><p></p><hr/><p></p><p><strong>Oven Technology</strong></p><p></p><p><strong>The Ovens: Magnificent Size and Performance.</strong></p><p>Any single or double combination oven you select will give you all the space you require, even for large dishes. Our 40-inch range has an oven capacity of up to 4 cubic feet.</p><p></p><p><strong>Accurate Electronic Temperature Control</strong></p><p>The electronic control makes sure that the oven's temperature doesn't change throughout, unlike in traditional ovens.</p><p></p><p><strong>4.3\\\" Touchscreen</strong></p><p>The display's superior readability is guaranteed by TFT technology, which provides instantaneous, clear graphics for each function.</p><p></p><p><strong>User-Friendly, Comprehensive, and High Resolution TFT Display.</strong></p><p>To control all of the features of the single oven or the two ovens with a single device, just touch the large display with one finger. With a single motion and a quick glance, you can control the temperature, timer, and automatic cooking start and end programmer.</p><p></p><p><strong>Soft-Closing Door</strong></p><p>A shock absorber installed in the door hinges allows for a more gradual and silent closing.</p><p></p><p><strong>Warming Drawer with Soft Closing System</strong></p><p></p><p><strong>Cooking Probe</strong></p><p>An indispensable tool for determining the core temperature, such as in meat cuts.</p><p></p><p><strong>Cooking with Steam</strong></p><p>You can select a drier or more moist cooking method thanks to this system, which removes the vapors from inside the cavity. You can produce a soft and juicy roast or a crispy baked dish in this manner.</p><p></p><p><strong>Temperature ranging from 85\\u00b0 to 575\\u00b0 F</strong></p><p>ILVE ovens make it simple to prepare intricate and sophisticated recipes with flawless results, from proofing to cooking, roasting to low temperature.</p><p></p><p><strong>High Density Insulation and Ventilation for Tangential Cooling</strong></p><p>prevents the kitchen and the furniture near the oven from getting too hot.</p><p></p><p><strong>For Complete Cleaning, Fold the Grill Coil</strong></p><p>The electric heating element of the grill can be lowered to more easily clean the upper portion of the cavity thanks to the articulated support.</p><p></p><p><strong>Easy Enamel Cleaning</strong></p><p>Grease can be cleaned more easily because it does not adhere to the surface.</p><p></p><p><strong>Functions of a Primary Oven 60 E3 TFT S UOV</strong></p><p></p><ul><li>Pizza service</li><li>Defrosting</li><li>Cooking intensively</li><li>Quick start</li><li>Cooking with lots of moisture</li><li>Cooking on a fan grill</li><li>Grill cooking with a closed door</li><li>Cooking from above</li><li>Cooking that is moist from above</li><li>Cooking from below</li><li>Cooking that is moist from below</li><li>Normal cooking that is static</li><li>Cooking that is moist and static</li><li>multiple fans cooking</li><li>multiple moist fans cooking</li><li>cooking ECO</li></ul><p></p><p><strong>Functions of the Secondary Oven UOV 30 E3 TFT</strong></p><p></p><ul><li>Grill cooking with a closed door</li><li>Cooking from above</li><li>Cooking from below</li><li>Normal cooking that is static</li><li>cooking ECO</li></ul><hr/><p></p><p><strong>Pizza Party</strong></p><p>Suitable for baking pizza, as well as bread and focaccia The lower heating element serves as the primary heat source and, along with the other underpowered heating elements, produces the ideal environment for this kind of cooking.</p><p></p><p><strong>Defrosting</strong></p><p>Assures that all frozen food is quickly defrosted and brought to room temperature without losing its flavor or appearance.</p><p></p><p><strong>Cooking Intensive</strong></p><p>With steam discharge, it guarantees quick and thorough cooking. Baked potatoes and vegetables, chicken, salt-crusted fish, etc. are advised for a crispy outcome.</p><p></p><p><strong>Quick Start</strong></p><p>With the quick preheating function, you can quickly reach your desired temperature before selecting the cooking mode that best suits your dish. When set to a low temperature, it also functions as a quick defrosting device.</p><p></p><p><strong>Cooking with Moisture</strong></p><p>The steam block ensures rapid and thorough cooking. It is advised for moist cooking, such as chicken cacciatore, braised meat, stewed rabbit, salt cod, etc.</p><p></p><p><strong>Cooking on a Fan Grill</strong></p><p>This function is especially quick and deep, and it saves a lot of energy. It can be used for a variety of foods, including game, pork chops, sausages, pork or mixed kebabs, and Roman-style gnocchi.</p><p></p><p><strong>Grill Cooking with a Closed Door</strong></p><p>Recommended for quick and deep grilling, browning, and roasting meat in general, fillet, Florentine steak, fish, and even vegetables.</p><p></p><p><strong>Cooking from Above</strong></p><p>It is especially good for browning and adding the last bit of color to many foods; it is the recommended function for burgers, pork chops, veal steaks, sole, cuttlefish, etc.</p><p></p><p><strong>Cooking with Moisture from Above</strong></p><p>Ideal for browning and giving many foods a final pop of color without sacrificing their tenderness.</p><p></p><p><strong>Cooking from the Ground Up</strong></p><p>Pastries (biscuits, meringues, leavened desserts, fruit desserts, etc.) are best cooked using this technique to finish the cooking cycle.</p><p></p><p><strong>Cooking Moist from Below</strong></p><p>This is the best cooking technique for finishing the cooking cycle while keeping the proper moisture content.</p><p></p><p><strong>Cooking Static Normal</strong></p><p>Pork chops, sausages, salt cod, braised meat, game, roast veal, meringues and biscuits, baked fruit, etc. can all be cooked in this traditional electric oven function.</p><p></p><p><strong>Cooking with Moist Static</strong></p><p>This increases the moisture content of typical static cooking.</p><p></p><p><strong>Cooking with Several Fans</strong></p><p>This feature enables cooking multiple dishes at once without the smells blending. Lasagna, croissants and brioches, tarts, cakes, etc. can be baked, saving time and electricity.</p><p></p><p><strong>Cooking with Several Moist Fans</strong></p><p>Multiple-fan cooking gains more moisture as a result.</p><p></p><p><strong>Cooking ECO</strong></p><p>This feature enables you to cook while using much less electricity. Braised meats, white meats, baked pasta, and delicate pastries are just a few examples of foods that benefit from slow roasting when using the ECO function. For frozen foods, this cooking cycle is not advised.</p><p></p><p><strong>Proposition 65 in California</strong></p><p>WARNING: Cancer and Reproductive Harm</p><p><a href=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/.\\\" rel=\\\"noopener\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">P65Warnings.ca.gov</a></p></div> <div><div> <div> <video controls=\\\"\\\" preload=\\\"auto\\\" src=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/qIZ8MSDCu-Y.mp4\\\" style=\\\"max-width:320px; margin-bottom:1.2rem;\\\">The video tag is not supported by your browser.</video> </div> <div> <video controls=\\\"\\\" preload=\\\"auto\\\" src=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/RRQlYvQPAMg.mp4\\\" style=\\\"max-width:320px; margin-bottom:1.2rem;\\\">The video tag is not supported by your browser.</video> </div> <div> <video controls=\\\"\\\" preload=\\\"auto\\\" src=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/Uh_EEzfUhUU.mp4\\\" style=\\\"max-width:320px; margin-bottom:1.2rem;\\\">The video tag is not supported by your browser.</video> </div> <div> <video controls=\\\"\\\" preload=\\\"auto\\\" src=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/wKi6ZYNcCxY.mp4\\\" style=\\\"max-width:320px; margin-bottom:1.2rem;\\\">The video tag is not supported by your browser.</video> </div> <div> <video controls=\\\"\\\" preload=\\\"auto\\\" src=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/re1Uo4qdmcc.mp4\\\" style=\\\"max-width:320px; margin-bottom:1.2rem;\\\">The video tag is not supported by your browser.</video> </div> <div> <video controls=\\\"\\\" preload=\\\"auto\\\" src=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/4JuPNm3uQqU.mp4\\\" style=\\\"max-width:320px; margin-bottom:1.2rem;\\\">The video tag is not supported by your browser.</video> </div> </div></div><br/><br/><strong>Freight Charges May Apply</strong><br/><br/></div></div> </div> <h3 class=\\\"station-tabs-tabtitle\\\"><span aria-controls=\\\"station-tabs-tabpanel_features\\\" aria-selected=\\\"false\\\" class=\\\"station-tabs-tab\\\" data-slug=\\\"features\\\" id=\\\"station-tabs-tab_features\\\" role=\\\"tab\\\" tabindex=\\\"-1\\\"> <span class=\\\"station-tabs-tabtext\\\">Features</span> </span></h3> <div aria-hidden=\\\"true\\\" aria-labelledby=\\\"station-tabs-tab_features\\\" class=\\\"station-tabs-tabpanel\\\" id=\\\"station-tabs-tabpanel_features\\\" role=\\\"tabpanel\\\"> <div class=\\\"station-tabs-tabcontent\\\"><div class=\\\"station-tabs-tabcontent\\\"> <div><div><div><li><strong>Enamel Oven Interior Cleaning Made Simple</strong></li></div><div>Grease can be cleaned more easily because it does not adhere to the surface.</div><div><img alt=\\\"Easy Clean Enamel Oven Interior\\\" src=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/1380.jpg\\\"/></div></div><div><div><li><strong>Burner in total black brass with nanotechnology-based non-stick coating</strong></li></div><div>A nanotechnological coating that guarantees easy cleaning and an elegant Total Black finish enhance the noble technical qualities of brass.</div><div><img alt=\\\"Total Black Brass Burner With Non-Stick Nanotechnological Coating\\\" src=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/1447.jpg\\\"/></div></div><div><div><li><strong>Cast Iron Pan Supports for the Cooktop (Hob)</strong></li></div><div>The pots are safely and effectively supported by the unbreakable cast iron pan supports.</div><div><img alt=\\\"Cooktop (Hob) With Cast Iron Pan Supports\\\" src=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/1448.jpg\\\"/></div></div><div><div><li><strong>Highly Customized Cooktops</strong></li></div><div>Choose your ideal combination of a gas burner cooktop or an induction cooktop, a mixed configuration, or a variety of setups thanks to the built-in AISI 304 steel and 12/10 thickness.</div><div><img alt=\\\"Highly Specialized Cooktops\\\" src=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/1449.jpg\\\"/></div></div><div><div><li><strong>Dual Gas Burners With Up To 20,000 BTU Power As Standard</strong></li></div><div>For all cooking methods, the ideal supply and distribution of heat.</div><div><img alt=\\\"Dual Gas Burners With Power Up To 20000 BTU As Standard\\\" src=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/1474.jpg\\\"/></div></div><div><div><li><strong>4.3-inch Touchscreen</strong></li></div><div>The display's superior readability is guaranteed by TFT technology, which provides instantaneous, clear graphics for each function. To control all of the features of the single oven or the two ovens with a single device, just touch the large display with one finger. With a single motion and a quick glance, you can control the temperature, timer, and automatic cooking start and end programmer.</div><div><img alt=\\\"4.3 Inch Full Touch Display\\\" src=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/1475.jpg\\\"/></div></div><div><div><li><strong>Ilve'S Magnificent Declaration</strong></li></div><div>A blend of modern technology and traditional Italian design that is both elegant and practical. Majestic is a daring, expert representation of the ideal range cooker that will adorn your house with its rounded shapes made of pure steel and meticulously crafted details.</div><div><img alt=\\\"Ilve\\u2019S Majestic Statement\\\" src=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/1496.jpg\\\"/></div></div><div><div><li><strong>The Statement Range Cooker That Makes Your Kitchen Special</strong></li></div><div>Aesthetics are important, but that's not all. To cook well and enjoyably, the best technologies are required. In order to consistently ensure the highest level of satisfaction, ILVE puts all of its research and experience to work for you, providing solutions that combine optimal performance with maximum simplicity, safety, and user-friendliness.</div><div><img alt=\\\"The Statement Range Cooker Which Makes Your Kitchen Unique\\\" src=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/1497.jpg\\\"/></div></div><div><div><li><strong>Pizza Party</strong></li></div><div>Suitable for baking pizza, as well as bread and focaccia The lower heating element serves as the primary heat source and, along with the other underpowered heating elements, produces the ideal environment for this kind of cooking.</div><div><img alt=\\\"Pizza Function\\\" src=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/5160.jpg\\\"/></div></div><div><div><li><strong>Cooking with Several Moist Fans</strong></li></div><div>Multiple-fan cooking gains more moisture as a result.</div><div><img alt=\\\"Multiple Moist Fan Cooking\\\" src=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/5161.jpg\\\"/></div></div><div><div><li><strong>Grill Cooking with a Closed Door</strong></li></div><div>Recommended for quick and deep grilling, browning, and roasting meat in general, fillet, Florentine steak, fish, and even vegetables.</div><div><img alt=\\\"Grill Cooking With Closed Door\\\" src=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/5162.jpg\\\"/></div></div><div><div><li><strong>From Below, Moist Cooking</strong></li></div><div>This is the best cooking technique for finishing the cooking cycle while keeping the proper moisture content.</div><div><img alt=\\\"Moist Cooking From Below\\\" src=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/5163.jpg\\\"/></div></div><div><div><li><strong>Defrosting</strong></li></div><div>Assures that all frozen food is quickly defrosted and brought to room temperature without losing its flavor or appearance.</div><div><img alt=\\\"Defrosting\\\" src=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/5164.jpg\\\"/></div></div><div><div><li><strong>Cooking Intensive</strong></li></div><div>With steam discharge, it guarantees quick and thorough cooking. Baked potatoes and vegetables, chicken, salt-crusted fish, etc. are advised for a crispy outcome.</div><div><img alt=\\\"Intensive Cooking\\\" src=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/5165.jpg\\\"/></div></div><div><div><li><strong>Cooking from the Air</strong></li></div><div>It is ideal for browning and adding the finishing touch of color to a variety of foods, such as burgers, pork chops, veal steaks, sole, cuttlefish, etc.</div><div><img alt=\\\"Cooking From Above\\\" src=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/5166.jpg\\\"/></div></div><div><div><li><strong>Cooking Static Normal</strong></li></div><div>Pork chops, sausages, salt cod, braised meat, game, roast veal, meringues and biscuits, baked fruit, etc. can all be cooked in this traditional electric oven function.</div><div><img alt=\\\"Static Normal Cooking\\\" src=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/5167.jpg\\\"/></div></div><div><div><li><strong>Quick Start</strong></li></div><div>The quick oven preheating feature enables it to reach the desired temperature quickly, and you can then select the best cooking mode for the dish. When a low temperature is set, it also functions as quick defrosting.</div><div><img alt=\\\"Quick Start\\\" src=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/5168.jpg\\\"/></div></div><div><div><li><strong>Cooking with Moisture</strong></li></div><div>The steam block ensures rapid and thorough cooking. It is advised for moist cooking, such as chicken cacciatore, braised meat, stewed rabbit, salt cod, etc.</div><div><img alt=\\\"Moist Intensive Cooking\\\" src=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/5169.jpg\\\"/></div></div><div><div><li><strong>From Above, Moist Cooking</strong></li></div><div>Ideal for browning and giving many foods a final pop of color without sacrificing their tenderness.</div><div><img alt=\\\"Moist Cooking From Above\\\" src=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/5170.jpg\\\"/></div></div><div><div><li><strong>Cooking with Moist Static</strong></li></div><div>This increases the moisture content of typical static cooking.</div><div><img alt=\\\"Moist Static Normal Cooking\\\" src=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/5171.jpg\\\"/></div></div><div><div><li><strong>Cooking with Several Fans</strong></li></div><div>This feature enables cooking multiple dishes at once without the smells blending. Lasagna, croissants and brioches, tarts, cakes, etc. can be baked, saving time and electricity.</div><div><img alt=\\\"Multiple Fan Cooking\\\" src=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/5172.jpg\\\"/></div></div><div><div><li><strong>Cooking on a Fan Grill</strong></li></div><div>This function is especially quick and deep, and it saves a lot of energy. It can be used for a variety of foods, including game, pork chops, sausages, pork or mixed kebabs, and Roman-style gnocchi.</div><div><img alt=\\\"Fan Grill Cooking\\\" src=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/5173.jpg\\\"/></div></div><div><div><li><strong>Cooking from the Ground Up</strong></li></div><div>Pastries (biscuits, meringues, leavened desserts, fruit desserts, etc.) are best cooked using this technique to finish the cooking cycle.</div><div><img alt=\\\"Cooking From Below\\\" src=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/5174.jpg\\\"/></div></div><div><div><li><strong>Cooking Green</strong></li></div><div>This feature enables you to cook while using much less electricity. Braised meats, white meats, baked pasta, and delicate pastries are all suitable for slow roasting thanks to the ECO function.</div><div><img alt=\\\"Eco Cooking\\\" src=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/5175.jpg\\\"/></div></div> </div> </div></div> </div> <h3 class=\\\"station-tabs-tabtitle\\\"><span aria-controls=\\\"station-tabs-tabpanel_specification\\\" aria-selected=\\\"false\\\" class=\\\"station-tabs-tab\\\" data-slug=\\\"specification\\\" id=\\\"station-tabs-tab_specification\\\" role=\\\"tab\\\" tabindex=\\\"-1\\\"> <span class=\\\"station-tabs-tabtext\\\">Specifications</span> </span></h3> <div aria-hidden=\\\"true\\\" aria-labelledby=\\\"station-tabs-tab_specification\\\" class=\\\"station-tabs-tabpanel\\\" id=\\\"station-tabs-tabpanel_specification\\\" role=\\\"tabpanel\\\"> <div class=\\\"station-tabs-tabcontent\\\"> <ul><li><strong>Brand</strong>: ILVE</li><li><strong>Series</strong>: Majestic II</li><li><strong>Appliance Category</strong>: Range</li><br/><p><strong>Appearance</strong></p><li><strong>Color</strong>: Antique White</li><li><strong>Color Family</strong>: Antique White</li><li><strong>Design Style</strong>: Retro Style</li><li><strong>Trim</strong>: Burnished</li><br/><p><strong>Dimensions</strong></p><li><strong>Exterior Width</strong>: 40\\u2033</li><li><strong>Width</strong>: 39 3/8\\u2033</li><li><strong>Depth</strong>: 29\\u2033</li><li><strong>Height</strong>: 38 3/8\\u2033</li><li><strong>Depth with Door Opened at 90 Degrees</strong>: 42 7/8\\u2033</li><li><strong>Product Weight (lbs)</strong>: 291</li><br/><p><strong>Fuel Type</strong></p><li><strong>Fuel Type</strong>: Electric</li><br/><p><strong>Style</strong></p><li><strong>Style</strong>: Freestanding</li><li><strong>Control Location</strong>: Front</li><br><p><strong>Capacity</strong></p><li><strong>Total Capacity (cu. ft.)</strong>: 3.82</li><li><strong>Number of Ovens</strong>: Double Oven</li><li><strong>Main Oven Capacity (cu. ft.)</strong>: 2.3</li><li><strong>Second Oven Capacity (cu. ft.)</strong>: 1.52</li><br><p><strong>Cooking Surface</strong></p><li><strong>Cooktop Configuration</strong>: Induction</li><li><strong>Burner/Element Type</strong>: Induction Element</li><li><strong>Number of Burners/Elements</strong>: 6</li><li><strong>Grill</strong>: No</li><li><strong>Griddle</strong>: No</li><li><strong>French Top</strong>: No</li><li><strong>Highest Element Output</strong>: 3200 Watts</li><li><strong>Burner/Element Output N1</strong>: 2500 Watts</li><li><strong>Burner/Element Output N2</strong>: 1800 Watts</li><li><strong>Burner/Element Output N3</strong>: 3200 Watts</li><li><strong>Burner/Element Output N4</strong>: 2500 Watts</li><li><strong>Burner/Element Output N5</strong>: 3200 Watts</li><li><strong>Burner/Element Output N6</strong>: 1800 Watts</li><br><p><strong>Oven</strong></p><li><strong>Oven Control Type</strong>: TFT Electronic Touchscreen</li><li><strong>Oven Door Type</strong>: Triple Glass Door</li><li><strong>Oven Cleaning Type</strong>: Easy Clean Enamel Cavities</li><li><strong>Main Oven Type</strong>: UOV 60 E3 TFT S</li><li><strong>Interior Width</strong>: 18 1/8\\u2033</li><li><strong>Interior Height</strong>: 14 1/8\\u2033</li><li><strong>Interior Depth</strong>: 16 1/8\\u2033</li><li><strong>Second Oven Type</strong>: UOV 30 E3 TFT</li><li><strong>Secondary Interior Width</strong>: 10 7/8\\u2033</li><li><strong>Secondary Interior Height</strong>: 14\\u2033</li><li><strong>Secondary Interior Depth</strong>: 17 1/3\\u2033</li><br><p><strong>Technical Details</strong></p><li><strong>Voltage</strong>: 240</li><li><strong>Amps</strong>: 75.6</li><br/><p><strong>Certifications</strong></p><li><strong>Star-K Certified</strong>: Yes</li><br/><p><strong>Warranty</strong></p><li><strong>Warranty</strong>: 2 Year Parts and Labor</li><br/><p><strong>Features</strong></p><li><strong>Sabbath Mode</strong>: Yes</li><li><strong>Display Type</strong>: TFT Display</li><li><strong>Number of Racks</strong>: 2 Rack</li><li><strong>Drawer</strong>: Warming Drawer</li><li><strong>Timer</strong>: Yes</li><li><strong>Temperature Probe</strong>: Yes</li><li><strong>Rotisserie</strong>: Yes</li><li><strong>Soft Close Door</strong>: Yes</li></br></br></br></br></ul> </div> </div> <h3 class=\\\"station-tabs-tabtitle\\\"><span aria-controls=\\\"station-tabs-tabpanel_shipping-returns\\\" aria-selected=\\\"false\\\" class=\\\"station-tabs-tab\\\" data-slug=\\\"shipping-returns\\\" id=\\\"station-tabs-tab_shipping-returns\\\" role=\\\"tab\\\" tabindex=\\\"-1\\\"> <span class=\\\"station-tabs-tabtext\\\">Shipping/Returns</span> </span></h3> <div aria-hidden=\\\"true\\\" aria-labelledby=\\\"station-tabs-tab_shipping-returns\\\" class=\\\"station-tabs-tabpanel\\\" id=\\\"station-tabs-tabpanel_shipping-returns\\\" role=\\\"tabpanel\\\"> <div class=\\\"station-tabs-tabcontent\\\">            Please review Castle &amp; Cabana's <strong>Return, Refund, Exchange</strong> and <strong>Shipping Policies</strong> carefully, as certain brands may have specific terms that differ from our general store policies.            <br/><br/>            For detailed information, please refer to the following sections:            <br/>            1. <strong><a href=\\\"/pages/refund-and-return-policy\\\">Refund and Return Policy</a></strong> <br/>            2. <strong><a href=\\\"/pages/shipping-policy\\\">Shipping Policy</a></strong> <br/><br/>            If you have any questions or require further clarification, our team is happy to assist you. Kindly contact us at: <strong><a href=\\\"mailto:sales@castleandcabana.com\\\">sales@castleandcabana.com</a></strong> <br/><br/> <strong>Note</strong>: Some items are available for pre-order with an estimated delivery time of 90-120 days, including custom-made products such as select sauna cabins, luxury appliances, and other special-order items. Other products may have shorter shipping times of 15-45 days, while most items are in stock and ready to ship within 1-2 business days. For more information about specific shipping timelines or our return policy, please contact our support team.            <p>Please note the shipping times are based on current market conditions and are subject to